items.name: The Sims Wiki
items.title: The Sims Wiki
items.headline: The Sims Wiki - the ultimate encyclopedia on The Sims
items.desc:
The Sims Wiki was founded in 2005 and is an encyclopedia devoted to The Sims series developed by Maxis and EA Games. With over 7,000 articles as of January 2013, it has a wide array of information for whatever aspect of the series you are looking for. We even have a dedicated namespace for fanon content where you can write about your own character's adventures.

Our community is very welcoming to new users and we have various different social aspects, such as an off-topic forum, Chat, an IRC channel, social media pages, a Steam group amongst other things to engage the community. So why not drop in, check the place out and get involved? Enjoy!

items.name: Forgotten Realms Wiki
items.title: Forgotten Realms Wiki
items.headline: Forgotten Realms Wiki
items.desc: The Forgotten Realms Wiki is an online wiki-based encyclopedia of the Forgotten Realms campaign setting for Dungeons & Dragons in all its editions. It aims to provide a complete and thorough reference work of the wealth of canon and licensed information, or "Realmslore", released in the decades since the setting's creation by Ed Greenwood. It covers the canonical sourcebooks and novels and other media, as well as officially licensed but non-canonical sources such as computer and video games and so on.

items.name: Simspedia

items.headline: Simspedia, encyklopedia o serii The Sims
items.desc:

Każdy użytkownik jest na niej mile widziany - zarówno początkujący, jak i zainteresowani gracze mogą dowiedzieć się na niej wielu ciekawych rzeczy.
Jeśli więc szukasz informacji o serii The Sims - to to jest dobre miejsce!

items.name: The New Systems Commonwealth Wiki
items.title: The New Systems Commonwealth Wiki
items.headline: Welcome to Andromeda!
items.desc:
Andromeda was conceived by Gene Roddenberry in the early 1970s and posthumously produced on his behalf by his widow Majel Barrett-Roddenberry. Captain Dylan Hunt is a member of the Systems Commonwealth's High Guard; he and his ship the Andromeda Ascendant are frozen in time. They awaken 300 years in the future, where Hunt discovers that the Commonwealth has fallen and the universe has fallen into chaos, with the strong preying on the weak. Deciding to change all of this, Hunt sets out with a new crew to create a new Commonwealth and bring order to a chaotic galaxy. With this impossible task in front of him, Dylan must come up with a way to convince races to sign up while fighting off some of the galaxy's most fearsome enemies, including the Magog (and their god the Spirit of the Abyss) and the Nietzscheans, whilst also dealing with the problems and betrayals of the members of his new crew.

"The long night has come. The Systems Commonwealth the greatest civilization in history has fallen. Now, one ship, one crew have vowed to drive back the night and rekindle the light of civilization. On the starship Andromeda hope lives again"

— Intro to Season One

"He is the last guardian of a fallen civilization, a hero from another time. Faced with a universe in chaos, Dylan Hunt recruits an unlikely crew and sets out to reunite the galaxies. On the starship Andromeda hope lives again "
— Intro to Season Two

"The Universe is a dangerous place. But in our future my crew and I fight to make it safe. I am Dylan Hunt, Captain of the Andromeda Ascendant, and these are our adventures."
— Intro to Seasons Three, Four and Five

A The Sims Wiki têm como objetivo oferecer conteúdo livre que qualquer um pode editar e melhorar para obter um banco de dados claro onde é possível encontrar todas as informações sobre The Sims.

items.name: Renaissance Kingdoms
items.title: Renaissance Kingdoms
items.headline: Explore the Renaissance Kingdoms Wiki!
items.desc: In Renaissance Kingdoms, you begin as a humble vagrant, in XVth Century Renaissant Europe, so the only way is up in terms of the social ladder. All the characters you will meet are players just like you: the carpenter, the baker you get your bread from, the miller who produces flour, the wholesaler who imports wheat from far-off distant lands... even the Mayor of your village, the county Sheriff, the Judge, Captains of the armies and the King or Queen of England! There are no NPCs (Non-player characters) at all in this game. All possible freedoms are left to players, including much darker roles: brigands, pirates, speculators, plotters of all types.

Gleichzeitig müsst ihr allerdings auf ihre Bedürfnisse achten: Sims wollen unterhalten, gepflegt und beschäftigt werden und haben ganz unterschiedliche Wünsche. Im Sims-Wiki könnte ihr euch über die erfolgreichste Lebenssimulation der Welt informieren.

items.name: Gongjin's Campaign Memorials
items.title: Gongjin's Campaign Memorials
items.headline: Welcome to Gongjin's Campaign Memorials: a Three Kingdoms Encyclopedia
items.desc:
Gongjin's Campaign Memorials is an editable encyclopedia dedicated to collect and consolidate everything known about the historical account of events of the Three Kingdoms period.


Three Kingdoms (''sānguó'' 三國) was an era of disunity. Following the loss of the de facto power of the Han Dynasty the land of China witnessed the rise of rival warlords Cao Cao 曹操, Liu Bei 劉備 and Sun Quan 孫權, each founding their rival states of Wei 魏, Shu-Han 蜀漢 and Wu 吳 effectively splitting the land of China in three.


Three Kingdoms' history has become legend through folklore collected in the 14th century novel ''Romance of the Three Kingdoms'' by Luo Guanzhong and in our modern era serves as a base for many movies (Red Cliff, The Assassins) and videogame series (Dynasty Warriors). The fiction has overshadowed the facts. How different are fact and fiction? Was Liu Bei truly a benevolent hero? Or a warlord who set his sights on power? Was Lü Bu truly the handsome unbested archer riding the era's fastest horse, Red Hare? And how beautiful was Diaochan?


Enter Gongjin's Campaign Memorials and be amazed, surprised or even disappointed when you learn the truth.
